    {
        "content": "<p>Coming from category theory, the name <code>BicartSq</code> feels very intuitive.</p>\n<p>For the peanut gallery, <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"488744\">@Jack McKoen</span> gave an example of a square like this in his LeanTogether2025 talk last week (in the lattice of subpresheaves, that <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"459699\">@Joël Riou</span> mentioned) where the right-hand inclusion relates the n-1 skeleton to the n-skeleton of a simplicial set.</p>",
